# HTTP verbs on Commands

Application Commands **sempre** começam com o verbo HTTP: `Post`, `Put`, `Patch`, `Delete`.

| Operação | Prefixo Command | Controller |
|----------|-----------------|------------|
| Criar | `Post{Entity}Command` | `[HttpPost]` |
| Substituir | `Put{Entity}Command` | `[HttpPut]` |
| Patch completo ModelWrapper | `Patch{Entity}Command` | `[HttpPatch]` |
| Transição / ação parcial | `Patch{Action}{Entity}Command` | `[HttpPatch("…/{action}")]` |
| Remover | `Delete{Entity}Command` | `[HttpDelete]` |

```text
✅ PatchAcceptOrganizationInviteCommand + [HttpPatch]
✅ PatchDeclineOrganizationInviteCommand
✅ PatchCancelOrganizationInviteCommand + [HttpPatch("{id}/cancel")] PatchCancel(...)
❌ AcceptOrganizationInviteCommand
❌ CancelOrganizationInviteCommand + [HttpPost("{id}/cancel")]
```

Domain Services continuam com verbo de domínio (`Create`/`Accept`/`Cancel`), não HTTP.

Detalhe: `.ai/PLAYBOOK/coding-style.md`.
